Build CRM Analytics Dashboards

To continuously monitor key metrics of your business, analyze results by key dimensions like region, products, and time period. Add interactive charts that synthesize information into an easy-to-read format. To complement the charts, add tables that show record-level details. Add filters to allow dashboard viewers to change the focus of the results.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

This section discusses how to build dashboards with the dashboard designer. Use a template to create a dashboard with a predefined design. Use wizards to quickly build widgets. Add, position, and align widgets in a dashboard using drag-and-drop, snap-to-grid, and browser reflow.

Create Dashboard Pages

Make information on a dashboard easier to digest by chunking content into multiple pages. This increases dashboard performance and allows you to tell a story by creating a dynamic pathway through your dashboard.

Add Widgets to the Dashboard

Widgets are basic building blocks of a dashboard. Add different widgets to perform functions, such as calculating key performance indicators, filtering dashboard results, visualizing data using interactive charts, and showing record-level details in tables.

Manage Queries for Widgets

Queries return results that are displayed in widgets. They can be built on a data source or created with user-defined values.

Make the Dashboard Widgets Interactive

You can make the widgets in CRM Analytics dashboards interactive. For example, filter a widget to show only results for the region selected in a list widget.

Set Initial Selections and Global Filters in the Dashboard

Set initial selections and global filters that appear when the dashboard first opens. The dashboard viewer can change them while viewing the dashboard.

Generate Unique CRM Analytics Dashboard Layouts for Different Devices

Optimize dashboards for viewing on smaller screens by removing widgets from a layout for mobile users and rearranging widgets for tablet-sized screens.

Keyboard Shortcuts for Building CRM Analytics Dashboards and Lenses

Run a performance check on the dashboard and its queries to ensure optimal performance. The dashboard inspector identifies bottlenecks and provides recommendations to improve performance.

Restore a Previous Version of a Dashboard

CRM Analytics uses version history to back up dashboard versions when you edit them so you can restore a previous version.

Collaborate on a New Dashboard Version Behind the Scenes

Users can add themselves to the list of dashboard publishers to edit and test new versions of the dashboard. Other users see a live version until a publisher makes the draft the live version.
